originalText:
::Chief Briggs' voice growls out of the navcom's tiny speaker.::

It was you, wasn't it? You were the mole in our ranks all along, you Southern bastard.
$(context.player.Name), this is Briggs. I want you to come to my tent ASAP. It's important. Over.
Attention all sec-troopers: We did it. The enemy has been defeated. I repeat: The enemy has been defeated. All defending troops should report to the supply tent. Out.
Attention all sec-troopers: The camp is under attack. I repeat - we are under attack.
$(context.player.Name), this is Marcus. Can you hear me, over?
$(context.npc_xpbl_oldfield_playerName), do you read me? This is Oldfield. Over.
$(context.player.Name), this is Briggs. What's your status? Over.
::Put the device back in your pocket.::
::Put the device back in your pocket.::
::Put the device back in your pocket.::
::Put the device back in your pocket.::
::Put the device back in your pocket.::
::Put the device back in your pocket.::
::Put the device back in your pocket.::
::Put the device back in your pocket.::
We'll find you. ::The conversation ends in static.::
All sec-troopers should report back. We need *everyone*!
All available troops should report to camp defense.
That technician with the waterproof comm - he's a pirate spy. He's been using that comm to leak information to the pirates ever since he arrived here, which happened at the same time as you arrived.

Excellent. I have work for you. We've been looking through some data in the Keep, or as we now know it as the Arch Island Keep, and have uncovered the locations of a couple of facilities I'd like you to investigate.
I need to speak to you in private. It's important. Please see me in my tent as soon as you're able to. Over.
Excellent. Bring it over to the camp ASAP. We'll be waiting for you outside of the Keep. Out.
We must locate one of these microchips before the natives regroup. You are to continue your search. Out.

::Mutie Refuge Dock - B6
Port Ceto Dock - G1
Northeastern Waters Area - I8
Sørmirbæren Geyser Village - J11::

::mut - b6
ceto - g1
wat - i8
bone - j11::
::Devs only. Data miners will be shot.::

The first one is the Nexus of Technology, a research facility located at coordinates K7. It should be your primary target for now, as we believe that, in addition to any potential technology we might uncover, it contains invaluable information regarding the other facilities and Lemurian history.
I'm here, Marcus. What's going on? Over.
::Put the device back in your pocket.::
You are all going to die.
This is $(context.player.Name). I'll be over there as soon as possible. Over.
I am unable to comply. You're without me this time. Good luck. Over.

Yes. He got really nervous when I called him to my tent and showed him the comm. After that it was just the matter of getting a few sec-troopers and asking the right questions. You have no idea how big this is, $(context.player.Name). Who knows what would've happened if that guy remained undetected. Over.
::Retype Ferryman's entries into something more readable.::
::Queue professor gives next mission delayed event.::
::Queue kidnapping of the professor delayed event.::
::Start mutant goes to Black Sea cutscene.::

Yes, Lemuria - this is the name NFT gave to this project as well as the whole region itself. 

Lemuria... But more on that later.
The matter is not of *utmost* urgency, but it is important and I'd rather delay it as little as possible. That is all. Oldfield out.
An ambush in the Keep. A team of sec-troopers opened the evacuation tunnels and engaged a group of pirates there.
It's about Professor Oldfield - he has been kidnapped. They stormed through one of the evacuation tunnels and took the professor. Over.
Negative. Return to the camp. This is an order. Out.
Damn it! We don't have enough men to defend the camp. Return as soon as possible or we might not survive this attack. Out.

They neutralized them all, however; no casualties on our side. Chief Briggs is on the scene right now if you need to speak with him. Everything's under control and you may resume with your missions as instructed. Just wanted to inform you. Over.
We locked him up for now. We're going to try getting more information from him.
Yes? ::You hear gunfire in the background.::
There's no need to use the navcom, $(context.player.Name), I'm right here. Out.
Briggs. ::You hear gunfire in the background.::
We've commenced the attack. Assist the sec-troops in locating and extracting the professor. Briggs out.
Too lazy to climb the lighthouse?
Yes? ::You hear gunfire in the background.:: Oldfield here. Who is this?
I'd prefer it if we spoke in person. Oldfield out.
::You hear a sigh.:: Just talk to me. Out.
This is RTA leader speaking, over.
::After a short delay and some jarring static.::
By the caverns, Arch Island Keep is a genuine gold mine of ancient history. In all honesty, if I don't get a heart attack now from all the excitement I don't think I ever will.
Things could've turned out a lot worse if I hadn't revealed the spy, over.

Chief Briggs wants you to meet him ASAP in the Keep, right at the entrance to the evacuation tunnels.

Over.
Good work, $(context.player.Name). Chief Briggs is pleased as well. You're getting a bonus for this.
I found the professor. Need extraction, over.
This is the one and only - Invictus.
I've got a gift for you...
Probably so, yes. He would've certainly tipped them off that the sec-troopers were coming their way.
And that first paycheck you didn't get originally.
That's it for now. Take care. Marcus out.
Good for the time being. Over. ::Gunfire continues.::
Our numbers are getting low, but we're still alive and kicking. Over. ::Gunfire continues.::
I found some old naval mines we could deploy around the island, over.
I've negotiated a deal with the pirates so we can get those mines. The conditions were that any passing boat has to pay a toll, and there can't carry any armed men, over.
The way to J1 is pirate-free. Go and get those mines, over.
You are all going to die.
I need backup. Can you spare any troops to attack the pirates, over?
Negative. We're pinned down. Attempting extraction at this point would be too risky.
Commence the attack on the pirates! Now!
I'm interested in the camp's security status, over.
Not before I get the chance to shoot your nuts off, bastard.
Not before I get the chance to blast that mug of yours to pieces, tart.
I'm interested in enemy activity, over.
I need to speak to you in person. Where can I find you? Over.
Can you see the Ferryman anywhere, over?
I need information on the pirate base. Over.
With great disdain. Farewell, $(context.npc_xpbl_oldfield_playerName). May this sea be your grave.
Don't worry about me. Best of luck. Out.
I have a report to make about Nexus of Technology, over.
I have a report to make about Crimson Meadow Horticulture Center, over.
I have a report to make about Lemurian Health Center, over.
I have a report to make about Joint Security Headquarters, over.
I have a report to make about the Abyssal Station, over.
I've found a submarine at the Blistering Shores facility in the northeastern part of the sea, at L12. Over.
Mind answering a couple of questions not related to my current mission?
Where are you right now, professor, at the Keep or in your tent? Over.
Doc, the muties want some of our medicine in exchange for letting me search for the microchip implant. I have a list of the medication they need, over.
Doc, we need to send some of our medical supplies to the muties, over.
About those supplies for the muties...
Doc, could you possibly implant a microchip into my hand, over?
Take it easy, banga, take it easy! Yer splittin' me ears.
Yea, yea, I can hear ye.
A gift? What kinda gift? Wait, who's dis?

Nexus of Technology, there is another location we have info on - Crimson Meadow Horticulture Center, located in H7; it's that misty red shore north-east of our camp. All of these red plants seem to originate from there. But be warned: Chief told me his sec-troopers encountered dangerous insectoid creatures over there.
Speak to the chief. He'll give you all the details. Over.
We don't have any sec-troopers left to spare.
In that case I'll dispatch an armed transport to the location you specified.
Negative. We're pinned down. I repeat: Negative, we're pinned down.
Lay low until we drive them away or find your own way out. Over.
On a small island at E4, over.
At G3, near the main entrance. The nearby enemies have been neutralized, over.
At G3, near the main entrance. The nearby enemies have been neutralized, and I'm about to open the gate for you, over.
The situation is bad. There are only a handful of sec-troopers left defending the camp.
There are currently $(context.global_xpbl_aegisSecTroopersAvailable) sec-troopers defending the camp.
Top of the lighthouse in the camp.
No. He sailed north into savage territory before I lost sight of him. Should be in my scope again soon.
You neutralized pretty much every fraggin' pirate.
They're well-armed, have lots of jet skis at their disposal - and hounds, lots of hounds walking about.
What do you want to know about?
It's you! May this sea be your grave.
Good work. I am all ears. Over.
Submarine? Oh, goodness me, that's quite a remarkable find. Shame it's so far away from here. How preserved is it, over?
You mean, over navcom? We better discuss these things in person, $(context.npc_xpbl_oldfield_playerName).
I'm in the Arch Island Keep, over.

::He answers with a delay.::

Does Chief know about this?
Why? We already have the implant.
::He sighs.:: We already have the implant. Why are we talking about this?
You do realize that is going out of our *actual* supplies? Not Union Resources or... I don't know what you have here in South Underrail. This will affect us. More for them means less for us.
Are you... out of your mind? You want to put... Wait, what implant? NFT's?

It's you, isn't it? 

We're gonna get you, treacherous bastard.
No hostiles in sight. Ready to move out, over.
I'm in position to load those naval mines, over.
The submarine is ready to be towed to the south-eastern part of the Black Sea. There's supposed to be an elevator there leading to a deep sea mining station. Over.
I need something moved to another location.

$(context.npc_xpbl_oldfield_playerName), there is one more important piece of information I need to give you. All of these coordinates came from a dispatching console found in Arch Island Keep. On it we found traffic logs between Arch Island Keep and these other locations; each of these has marked coordinates. Other facilities must have them as well, so if you find them in working condition, get us those coordinates. It will help us immensely.
At J1. They appear to be in good condition. I just need you to send someone to pick them up, over.
Especially considering they'd have to go through pirate territory.
Having sec-troopers out of the camp at a moment like this is far too risky.
Lay low until we drive them away if you can; if not - you're on your own, soldier. Over.
Affirmative. We'll be right there. Out.
Our firearm and ammunition supplies are
The sea's looking calm at the moment. No enemy activity whatsoever.
He follows a fairly consistent route, visiting the mutie island and the pirate base before going north again. Over.
pier on the southern side of the mutie island.
Locate the professor and carry out his extraction, over.
Lots of fraggin' pirates here, that's for sure.
I don't think you understand. I believe it could still be used, even if not to its full capacity, over.
I don't think you understand. It's a functional submarine. It's damaged and cannot be used to its full capacity, but it has an auto-pilot I may be able to activate, over.

I don't think you understand. It's a functional submarine. It's damaged and cannot be used to its full capacity, but I've found a way to activate its auto-pilot. I've located this Abyssal Station Zero in the southeastern bay, and that's where I'll be diving, over.
See me when you return to the camp and I'll be happy to answer any questions you may have. Over.
Yes. He told me to contact you.

::[Intelligence]:: Yes. I can't get past a bioscanning chamber at the military base to the north, and it has to be because I'm using the arm, yet without the arm I can't get authorized. So maybe if I implant the chip in my own hand I'll be able to pass the scan. Over.
Yes. I can't get past a bioscanning chamber at the military base to the north. Maybe if I put that thing in my hand I'll be able to. Over.

::[Intelligence]:: I can't get past a bioscanning chamber at the military base to the north, and it has to be because I'm using the arm, yet without the arm I can't get authorized. So maybe if I implant the chip in my own hand I'll be able to pass the scan. Over.
I can't get past a bioscanning chamber at the military base to the north. Maybe if I put that thing in my hand I'll be able to, over.
We've been ambushed by a giant hermit crab. Neutralized it before it could get close. This one was hiding in an NFT crate. Be on the lookout.

We recently engaged giant insects capable of long-ranged attacks. They live in three to four meters tall hives and are highly defensive. We're trying to avoid these hives as much as possible but there is simply too many of them.
We engaged a group of natives. Neutralized one, the rest retreated. No casualties on our sides.

Nothing t--

::You hear loud screeching followed by silence.::
We're holding position, over. ::You hear gunfire in the background.:: Eat this! ::Gunfire continues.::
We're... we're low on men... ::You hear gunfire in the background.:: There are so many... ::Gunfire continues.::
::He answers after a pause.:: It's just me here. Everything's calm. Over.

Our defenses are spread real thin. I don't know if we can take another attack.

Over.
We're starting to feel the casualties, but so far so good. Everything is in order otherwise, and no hostiles in sight. Over.
Everything is in order. No hostiles in sight, over.
Business as usual. No hostile activities, over.
We're... trying to pick off as many as we can... ::You hear gunfire and water splashing in the background.::
Perimeter is secured. We're staying on patrol until the last ship leaves the island, over.

The insects northeast have become more aggressive, engaging passing patrols from greater distance. 

There are no friendly casualties, over.
Recently encountered green serpents. Scared them off. Nothing else to report. Over.

A previously unreported kind of serpent attacked Sierra-Seven. He's okay. The snake has retreated after being wounded. It's blue in color, larger than the other types and capable of spitting caustic projectiles at great distances. Highly dangerous. Be on the lookout. Over.
All is clear at the moment.

So, how ye likin' me girl, eh, ye back-bladin' rat? Huh? HUH? Oh, I found out, I sure did. Now lemme tell ye a lid'l secret: By tomorrow ye'll be fish chomp. 

Yer fish chomp, banga...

Jenny... I heard sumthin', Jenny. I heard ye had sum dam' bangin' time wit' dat Jimmy D' Barrel. I was a clod fer trustin' a floozy who gave it to a fat, stinkin' deucer d' momen' I turned 'round.

Yer fish chomp. Yer both fish chomp, ye fisheyed serpent!
Mhm. I know whe-- ::static.:: --soon-- ::static.:: --aiting for you there.
I'm at $(context.npc_xpbl_ferryman_currentLocation). ::You hear him puffing smoke directly into the microphone.::
That is all. Best of luck, $(context.npc_xpbl_oldfield_playerName). Contact me over the navcom or in person once you've uncovered something. Oldfield out.
It's too dangerous to go through the pirate territory.
If you say so. In that case I'll dispatch some laborers to the location you specified.
The area has been secured, but still be on the lookout for any creepers. The whole region is infested with them, over.
The whole region is infested with creepers, and so is the area where the mines are. Tell them to be on the lookout, over.
He's lying on the ground and doesn't appear to be moving. Looks fragged to me. Over.

From what I've been able to gather so far, there are three locations where Professor Oldfield is most probably being held at: The first is a derelict battleship in G2, right in the middle of their main base. Then there's a large heavily-defended building in E3. And then there's also that smaller base in I5, the one with the NFT lighthouse. There's a lot of activity there as well, which makes it another potential target.

::After listening to you with great interest, only occasionally interjecting with various exclamations of surprise and awe, the professor shares his thoughts.::

Goodness me, that is marvelous indeed! Your descent down the elevator shaft, turning on the power, exploring the floors, all of it - truly incredible. And the fact that you managed to upgrade your microchip implant's clearance level with that... what did you say the device was called?

::You manage to convey the brooding atmosphere of the horticulture center so perfectly that the professor remains speechless for a good half a minute after you've finished speaking. He speaks after this pause.::

By the caverns, that is un-believable, $(context.npc_xpbl_oldfield_playerName). The vegetation, the insects, the pesticide... amazing, truly amazing.

::The surreal nature of your visit to the Lemurian Health Center is difficult to express in mere words, but you do your best, and the professor follows your report with interest till the very end.::

I... don't know what to say, $(context.npc_xpbl_oldfield_playerName).

::You report all your findings while the professor, as always, listens with great attentiveness.::

A rather sad ending for the Lemurian Security Command, I have to say. Goodness me, you stood in the same room from which Lemurian officers, fathers, sons and husbands observed their home being demolished by the Biocorp Undernavy.
Not at all, $(context.npc_xpbl_oldfield_playerName), not at all.
Wait a minute, you mean an *actual* working submarine. By the caverns!
I can't help you. We have the implant already and can't afford to be wasting resources.
Well, when you put it that way...
Uh... I'm not following you at all, but I still can't do that.
Sorry, $(context.player.Name), but I can't do that.
Everything's okay. Your voice disturbed some bats. We have nothing new to report.

Several patrols have reported spotting something large passing underneath them, serpentine in shape and over fifteen or even twenty meters long. Outside of that the descriptions wildly differ.

I hope it's just fatigue, but be ready for anything. Over.
The waters are calm at the moment.
Well, git off. 'S fer important business 'n' d' Cap'n said dere can't be anyone on d' frequency but me 'n'... mates. So don' be a dumbat 'n' get off, c'mon.
Yes, both the warehouse and the dock outside, over.
The warehouse is clear, but there are still creatures at the dock outside, just east, over.
The dock outside is clear, but there are still creatures in the warehouse, over.
No. There are still creatures both inside the warehouse and at the dock outside, just east.
I've negotiated a deal with the pirates. You'll have to pay a toll, and there can't be any armed men on the boats, over.
The way to J1 is free. Don't you worry about the pirates, over.
What do you propose I do, over?
Roger that. Dispatching units now. Out.
But for all we know the professor could be held anywhere. Maybe they even moved him somewhere deeper in the bay. Over.

High sheet metal walls around the base, with manned turrets at regular intervals. The southern entrance is the least defended one, but to get there you have to sneak through either G4 or H4, cross the bay undetected, and then enter the base from there. Plenty of jet ski patrols in the bay as well. Over.

Appears to be one of those old Biocorp ships of war. There is a bridge which connects the main platform to the ship. Heavily guarded. If I were the captain of this rancid rabble, that's where I'd like my HQ to be. Over.

It's a two-story building. Purpose unknown. Multiple entrances. Lots of guards outside, and there are snipers on the rooftop. There are two ways to enter the area, east and south, and both require you to go through the main base. The western path leads up to a hill; it leads to the cliff where that glowing monolith is at. Over.

Tall sheet metal walls. Jet ski dock at the entrance. Two large buildings, the taller of which is connected to the lighthouse via skyway. Actually, that's three buildings if we count the lighthouse as well. The main entrance is heavily guarded. But there is another entrance to the east. That's all I got. Over.
But one of the most important things is that you managed to find that dispatch console. They seem to be the key to discovering the locations of Lemurian facilities.
It's... such a shame you couldn't explore the entire facility. Who knows what other incredible things you would've discovered?
Goodness me... It's best that we discuss this in the camp. Come here as soon as you can. Out.
::He sighs.:: Alright, alright. Read me the list.

Hm. 

I can't give them everything they need. That's... just ludicrous. I'll check my inventory and see what I can do.
I don't have the proper tools, and not to mention all the other risks I see with a procedure like that in these conditions.
::You hear nothing. Even though you can't see him, you get the feeling that he just nodded.::
Uh, perhaps there is some other way...
The whole south-eastern part of the sea is pretty much dead. Barely any pirate activity there.
Lots of pirate jet ski patrols about. They could be up to something
Not much activity over at the pirate base. Their patrols are becoming rather sparse as well.
Haven't noticed any activity lately. No moving lights, boats or anything of the sort.
Not much activity lately. Much fewer moving lights and boats as well.
Less activity than before the first attack, but still plenty.
Still lots of activity. There's a lot of them there.
Lots of activity there ever since we moved in. They are probably preparing for another attack.
Ah, yes - microchip encoder. That clearance level will certainly prove to be of great use, certainly.
It might indeed be for the best.
After being here for this long there's nothing I find hard to believe anymore, $(context.npc_xpbl_oldfield_playerName).
Indeed we should, yes. Was there a reason why you did that?

Yes... Yes. It's an interesting parallel to make, as fifteen years ago Biocorp Armed Forces officers too were looking down at Protectorate invaders breaking into and causing havoc in Dis. 

History tends to repeat itself, yet sadly it seems that with each iteration humanity loses more than it rebuilds, and some things are lost forever.
Acorn? ::He takes off his glasses for a moment.:: Could it be? How large is it then if...?

No, no. Sorry, $(context.player.Name), but I can't help you. I can't afford to be wasting resources. And Chief Briggs... 

Just forget about it, okay?
Now, was there anything else you needed or...?

But if you still find a way to do it... ::He sighs.:: I got an extraction tool I use for... Oh, what do you even care.

If you get yourself an implant, I can get it out. Over.
Dis is Lord Git off D' Damned Frequency!
Yes. Six hundred, as was the deal. Over.
Yes. Seven hundred, as was the deal. Over.
Yes. Eight hundred, as was the deal. Over.
Yes. One thousand, as was the deal. Over.
We haven't seen him in a while, but maybe that old ferryman would be willing to help you.
Maybe that old ferryman would be willing to help you.
This might be the calm before the storm.

Lots of firearms, explosive weapons, crossbows, machetes, sledgehammers and other melee weapons. Large-caliber, double-barreled turrets; no energy weapons noticed so far.

They also have hounds, pit bulls mostly. Was almost sniffed out by one of those mutts during my infiltration.

Over.
I needed it to access Joint Security headquarters. There was a scanner there which wouldn't let me pass without an implant in my hand.
I need it to access Joint Security headquarters. There is a scanner there which won't let me pass without an implant in my hand.
I had a feeling I'd need that at some later point. Better do it while I'm there.
And it... it is at that Abyssal Station? Abyssal Station Zero.
But this Abyssal Station you're talking about... It is something completely new to me.
This submarine, $(context.npc_xpbl_oldfield_playerName), it could be the last part of the puzzle. If the Acorn truly is down there, at this Abyssal Station...
This would certainly open a new way for us to access these facilities. There would be no need to traverse dangerous waters, but we can instead sail below the surface.
::You wait for Doc's response after reading him the list.::
Yes. I'll send someone over. ::He sighs.:: Savage out.
He's been uncooperative so far, but who knows. That's all I could think of. Over.
See Marcus about your well-earned bonus when you come back.

The sec-chef, yes, the sec-chef is in charge of payments now. You'll find him in the camp's kitchen.

::It takes a moment for him to continue.:: He's... one of the few left alive, I'm afraid.
See the sec-chef about your bonus when you come back.
Ah, yes, I believe you mentioned it to me.
Seems so. The location is marked as Abyssal Station Zero Elevators.
Exactly. And from this station I've just returned.
The location is marked as Abyssal Station Zero Elevators. It is somewhere in the southeastern bay.
To Abyssal Station Zero. From which I've just returned.
The only question which remains is: Will this submarine actually work?
It's right past the Pirate Bay, then you go... ::Explain to him how to reach you and help him load the naval mines.::
I'll contact you as soon as I have a new task for you. Best of luck. Oldfield out.
I believe Doctor Savage can extract the implant for you.

It's rather peculiar: This entire region has always been referred to as LEMCO, and we've not found a single instance of this Abyssal Station being mentioned.

Yet... if this station truly is abyssal, its depth could have saved it from Biocorp's detection.
Our jet ski numbers are very good.
We have a sufficient number of jet skis left.
We have lost a large number of jet skis.
We barely have any jet skis left.

::He removes his glasses and begins wiping them, as if sharpening his thoughts by sharpening his vision.:: The Acorn... they sent it to a place they deemed the safest. They must've sent people too. If this station has remained intact for so long...

::He puts his glasses back on.:: $(context.npc_xpbl_oldfield_playerName)... there could still be someone down there.
It's what NFT does best. Conquering the most inhospitable places.

You may become the first $(#man/woman) in two centuries to dive in a Lemurian submarine. 

If you need anything, contact me. We're getting so close...
In addition to that we have lost
This is your next destination, $(context.npc_xpbl_oldfield_playerName), Abyssal Station Zero.
In case that these elevators are no longer functional, there is still that submarine you can try to use. Although... I fear whether it could endure the depths.
Hopefully those elevators still work. If not... There has to be another way. There has to be.
See Marcus about your well-earned bonus when you come back.

The sec-chef, yes, the sec-chef is in charge of payments now. You'll find him in the camp's kitchen.

::It takes a moment for him to continue.:: He's... one of the few left alive, I'm afraid.
See the sec-chef about your bonus when you come back.
Best of luck, $(context.npc_xpbl_oldfield_playerName), best of luck. Oldfield out.
